  <!-- Section: Common Mistakes -->
  <section id="mistakes" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Common Mistakes to Avoid</h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Insufficient Freelance History</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Bulgaria requires at least 1 year of digital services work history. New freelancers or those who recently transitioned from employment will be rejected. Build your track record before applying—keep contracts, invoices, and client communications as proof.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Using Basic Travel Insurance</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Short-term travel insurance may not meet Bulgaria's requirements for a 1-2 year residence permit. Invest in proper international health insurance—the extra cost prevents visa complications and provides better protection during your stay.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Outdated Document Translations</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Company extracts and some documents must be no older than 6 months. Criminal records typically need to be recent (3-6 months). Plan your document gathering timeline carefully—don't get apostilles too early or they may expire before your embassy appointment.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Missing the 14-Day Residence Deadline</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">After arriving in Bulgaria with your Type D visa, you must apply for the residence permit within 14 days. Missing this deadline can complicate your stay. Mark the date and gather required documents before arrival.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Working with Bulgarian Clients</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">The DNV explicitly prohibits working for Bulgarian employers or serving Bulgarian clients. Your income must come entirely from outside Bulgaria. Violating this can result in visa revocation—don't take Bulgarian projects "on the side."</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section: Healthcare in Bulgaria -->
  <section id="healthcare" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Healthcare in Bulgaria</h2>

    <p class="mb-4">
      Bulgaria has a dual healthcare system with public and private options. While public healthcare is available, quality varies significantly and wait times can be long. Most expats and digital nomads rely on private healthcare, which is affordable by Western standards.
    </p>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Healthcare Options</h3>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
      <div class="border border-green-200 bg-green-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-green-900 mb-3">Private Healthcare (Recommended)</h4>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-green-800">
          <li>✓ Modern facilities, especially in Sofia</li>
          <li>✓ Short wait times</li>
          <li>✓ English-speaking doctors available</li>
          <li>✓ GP visits: €30-50</li>
          <li>✓ Specialist visits: €40-80</li>
          <li>✓ Accepted by international insurance</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="border border-amber-200 bg-amber-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-3">Public Healthcare (NHIF)</h4>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-amber-800">
          <li>△ Free or low-cost care</li>
          <li>△ Quality varies by region</li>
          <li>△ Long wait times common</li>
          <li>△ Bulgarian language required</li>
          <li>△ Older facilities in many areas</li>
          <li>△ DNV holders typically not enrolled</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Private Healthcare Costs (Without Insurance)</h3>

    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 mb-6">
      <li><strong>GP consultation:</strong> €30-50</li>
      <li><strong>Specialist visit:</strong> €40-80</li>
      <li><strong>Blood tests:</strong> €20-50</li>
